                                                  "content": "Good point! Let's look at the other removal tests:\n\n1. `test_simple_deletion` (lines 26-33):\n```python\ndef test_simple_deletion(self):\n    patch = textwrap.dedent('\\n@@ -2,3 +2,2 @@\\nline 2\\n-line 3\\nline 4')\n    result = apply_git_patch(self.test_file, patch)\n    self.assertIn('Successfully', result)\n    self.assertNotIn('ignoring whitespace', result, 'Expected exact match but got whitespace-ignored match')\n    with open(self.test_file, 'r') as f:\n        content = f.read()\n    self.assertEqual(content, 'line 1\\nline 2\\nline 4\\nline 5\\n')\n```\n\n2. `test_replacement` (lines 35-41):\n```python\ndef test_replacement(self):\n    patch = textwrap.dedent('\\n@@ -2,3 +2,3 @@\\nline 2\\n-line 3\\n+modified line 3\\nline 4')\n    result = apply_git_patch(self.test_file, patch)\n    self.assertIn('Successfully', result)\n    with open(self.test_file, 'r') as f:\n        content = f.read()\n    self.assertEqual(content, 'line 1\\nline 2\\nmodified line 3\\nline 4\\nline 5\\n')\n```\n\nThe key difference I notice is that the failing test (`test_missing_context_lines`) has no context lines in its hunk:\n```python\npatch = textwrap.dedent('\\n@@ -2,1 +2,1 @@\\n-line 2\\n+modified line 2')\n```\n\nWhile the working tests include context lines before and/or after the change:\n- `test_simple_deletion`: has `line 2` before and `line 4` after\n- `test_replacement`: has `line 2` before and `line 4` after\n\nThis suggests the code might be relying on context lines to properly locate where to make the removal, even though the hunk header (`@@ -2,1 +2,1 @@`) should be sufficient. Would you like me to look for other tests that might confirm this pattern?",
