                                                                                                                                  "content": "Looking at each line number's behavior:\n\n```\nLine 1:\nGot:     line 1, line 2, line 3, line 4, line 5, modified line 1, line 6\nExpected: modified line 1, line 2, line 3, line 4, line 5, line 6\nPattern: Adds new content near end, doesn't remove anything\n\nLine 2:\nGot:     modified line 2, line 2, line 3, line 4, line 5, line 6\nExpected: line 1, modified line 2, line 3, line 4, line 5, line 6\nPattern: Removes line 1, adds new content at start\n\nLine 3:\nGot:     line 1, line 2, modified line 3, line 3, line 4, line 5, line 6\nExpected: line 1, line 2, modified line 3, line 4, line 5, line 6\nPattern: Adds new content at correct spot, doesn't remove old line\n\nLine 4:\nGot:     line 1, line 2, modified line 4, line 4, line 5, line 6\nExpected: line 1, line 2, line 3, modified line 4, line 5, line 6\nPattern: Removes line 3, adds new content at line 3\n\nLine 5:\nGot:     line 1, line 2, line 3, modified line 5, line 5, line 6\nExpected: line 1, line 2, line 3, line 4, modified line 5, line 6\nPattern: Removes line 4, adds new content at line 4\n\nLine 6:\nGot:     line 1, line 2, line 3, line 4, modified line 6, line 6\nExpected: line 1, line 2, line 3, line 4, line 5, modified line 6\nPattern: Removes line 5, adds new content at line 5\n```\n\nThe pattern appears to be:\n1. For removals: It's removing the line at (target_line - 1)\n2. For additions: \n   - For line 1: adds near the end\n   - For other lines: adds at (target_line - 1)\n\nThis suggests there's a consistent off-by-one error in both the removal and addition logic, but with a special case for line 1 additions that's putting them near the end instead.\n\nWould you like me to add some more test cases to verify this pattern, particularly around the line 1 special case?",
